This paper is primarily focused on image recognition using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of residual connections on learning, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents new architectures for Inception networks, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the models on the ImageNet classification challenge, which is a task related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
